# ⭐ Repository Overview

This repository contains the complete implementation of **Week 1** of the **Cognizant DN 5.0 Deep Skilling Program**.

The objective of this repository is to understand the most important **Object-Oriented Design Principles** and **Gang of Four (GoF) Design Patterns** through practical C# implementations.

Every exercise has been implemented as an individual **Console Application**, making it easy to understand and execute independently.

---

# 🎯 Objectives

After completing this repository you will understand

- Object-Oriented Programming
- Design Patterns
- SOLID Principles
- Loose Coupling
- High Cohesion
- Reusability
- Maintainability
- Extensibility
- Clean Code Practices
- Software Design Principles

---

# 📖 What are Design Patterns?

Design Patterns are reusable solutions to commonly occurring software design problems.

Instead of solving the same problem repeatedly, software engineers use proven design patterns to create flexible, maintainable, and scalable applications.

Benefits

- Improve Code Reusability
- Improve Maintainability
- Reduce Code Duplication
- Increase Scalability
- Improve Software Architecture
- Reduce Development Time

---

# 📖 What is SOLID?

SOLID is a collection of five design principles introduced to improve software maintainability and flexibility.

SOLID stands for

| Letter | Principle |
|---------|-----------|
| S | Single Responsibility Principle |
| O | Open Closed Principle |
| L | Liskov Substitution Principle |
| I | Interface Segregation Principle |
| D | Dependency Inversion Principle |

Following these principles helps developers build applications that are easier to extend and maintain.

